Then, place amṛta on their tongues. {391}
Meditate that the blissful taste of amṛta courses thrillingly through your whole body. That is the point of the secret abhiṣeka.
Meditate that the essence of that bliss is nonconceptual. That is the prajñājñāna abhiṣeka.

