Arrange food and drink, the substances of method and wisdom, and so on, according to what is appropriate. Consecrate them as done for the amṛta. {462}
The feast items are inexhaustible sense pleasures, excellent and vast. Their unimaginable arrangement pervades the earth and everywhere in between.
Thus, contemplate.

I request the gurus, victors, and their sons and daughters, {500}
for the sake of all beings,
to turn the wheel of dharma
so its blazing light may dispel the darkness.

Outer caṇḍālī has qualities similar to fire. One piece of wood thrown into a fire will be burned, and one hundred pieces thrown in a fire will be burned. Similarly, the harm of one spirit will be burned, and the harm of a hundred will be burned. {503}
Inner caṇḍālī has qualities similar to medicine. When a skilled doctor dispenses medicine, a disease is cured. Similarly, by cultivating caṇḍālī, diseases are cured. Secret caṇḍālī has qualities similar to lions. In the same way that lions overpower all wild herbivorous animals, cultivating caṇḍālī overpowers all mental afflictions.
Suchness caṇḍālī has qualities similar to mirrors. When we look into a clear mirror, we see our face. Similarly, by cultivating caṇḍālī, we see vividly our own awakened wisdom, and therefore we have the thought, “Oh! It is right here. I just didn’t recognize it before.”[9]

By preventing the release of bindu
through the nine orifices, these trulkhors are the supreme vital points.
They confer longevity and inconceivable excellent qualities.[48] (156–58) {537}

You will live long without getting old. {541}
You will not experience the subsiding of channels or wrinkles.
You will be youthful and have spectacular beauty.[31] (148–50)
